<Class name="CM_TrxControlAgent" id="60d17025-b658-4691-8d76-7fe97de8a4f9">
    <superclass name="CM_TransactionAgent"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <abstract/>
    <text>These classes control the transactions that perform updates to
the database. You may call any CM_UtilityAgent method if you bracket
it in a begin/close transaction pairing from outside. The methods
in these classes do the enclosure of begin/commit transaction.

You may have a lot of Interface calles to make and want them all in
one transaction. Add them to these classes.
The validation methods as well may be called as a part of this
process.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="cmtrans"/>
